        <h2 id="verdict">Is Plausible worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For privacy-conscious sites: absolutely.</strong> At $9/mo, Plausible's script speed, GDPR posture, and 30-second dashboard are excellent value. The 10–18% traffic recovery from removing the cookie banner alone often justifies the switch.</p>

        <p><strong>For attribution-heavy marketing teams:</strong> Plausible may feel light. Pair with Hotjar/Clarity for behavioral context, or stay on GA4 for funnels.</p>

        <p><strong>For SMBs whose real problem is traffic, not measurement:</strong> Plausible tells you the dashboard is empty. theStacc fills it.</p>

