        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is Plausible Analytics?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Plausible is a privacy-first, lightweight web analytics tool that replaces Google Analytics with a sub-1KB script, GDPR-compliant tracking (no cookies, no banners needed), and a clean dashboard you can understand in 30 seconds. It is open source and can be self-hosted for free.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How much does Plausible cost in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Growth $9/mo (10K pageviews, 1 site). Business $19/mo (100K pageviews, up to 50 sites). Enterprise custom. Self-hosted Community Edition is free (AGPL). Annual billing saves 2 months (about 16.7% off). Non-profits get 15% off Business annual.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Is Plausible better than Google Analytics 4?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For most small to mid-market sites: yes. Plausible is faster, GDPR-compliant out of the box, and simpler. GA4 has deeper analysis, more integrations, and a free tier. Pick Plausible for privacy + speed + simplicity. Pick GA4 for granular attribution and advanced segmentation.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Is Plausible GDPR compliant?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Plausible uses no cookies and collects no personal data, so it falls outside GDPR consent requirements in most EU jurisdictions. Many sites remove their cookie banner entirely after switching, recovering 10–18% of traffic that was previously bouncing on the banner.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Can I self-host Plausible for free?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — Plausible Community Edition is open source under AGPL. You can self-host on your own server. Most users land on a $5–$24/mo VPS (Hetzner or DigitalOcean). Setup takes about 30 minutes with Docker.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Does Plausible have a free tier?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No, the cloud-hosted product does not have a free tier — it starts at $9/mo for 10K pageviews. The open-source Community Edition is fully free to self-host. Cloud has a 30-day free trial.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Is Plausible worth it in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For privacy-conscious small to mid-market sites: yes. At $9/mo, the script speed, GDPR posture, and 30-second dashboard are excellent value. For attribution-heavy marketing teams that depend on UTM-level segmentation, it may feel light.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Plausible vs Fathom — which is better?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Both are privacy-first and lightweight. Fathom starts at $15/mo, has a slightly prettier dashboard, and no self-hosting. Plausible starts at $9/mo, is open source, and ships a smaller script. Plausible wins on price and transparency; Fathom on dashboard polish.</p></div></div>
          </div>
